Event Sentence: The question is when we allow policemen across the hierarchy to avail transfers, why not constables, who comprise 90 per cent of the force.The officer said that already there are several thousand applications pending across the state for long and the amendment was necessary to clear them in next few days.As per the latest amendments, constables who have completed eight years of service in a given unit are eligible for applying and availing the benefit of being transferred to a district of their choice.Under this amendment, constables can apply for inter-district transfer on completion of three years provided there is a medical emergency in his/her family or under husband-wife posting at same station scheme.Senior police officers at the DG office maintained that women constables, who after getting married in a district other than the one they are posted, are most likely to benefit with this amendment.Under this amendment, the establishment board formed at all the units in the state, with the respective SP/commissioner of police as head of the board, has been empowered to directly communicate with the unit commanders from other units and take a call on inter-district transfers of constables.
Headline: Unit commanders to police constable transfers
